decision_conditions:
Condition : 7 - The illuminated advertisement hereby approved shall comply with the following terms:
(a) Between the hours of sunset and sunrise, the intensity of the illumination of the advertisement shall not exceed 300 cd/m2 as recommended by the Institution of Lighting Professionals (ILP, PLG05) or maximum limits as permitted by any guidance that supersedes this;
(b) Between the hours of  sunrise and sunset, either no lighting, or the maximum illumination of the advertisement shall not exceed 3500 cd/m2 as recommended by the Institution of Lighting Professionals (ILP, PLG05) or maximum limits as permitted by any guidance that supersedes this;
(c) The advertisement shall be fitted with a light intensity monitoring censor to ensure the illuminance intensity is dimmable to take account of ambient light conditions and comply with the maximum recommended lighting intensity; 
(d) The advertisement shall not display any moving, or apparently moving, images; 
Reason: In the interests of amenity and highway safety.
